<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="123" type="comments">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="123">Comments.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="123">
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1111/zoj.12102" author="Moraes, SS" journalOrPublisher="Zoological Journal of the Linnean Society" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" pagination="362 - 399" refId="B28" refString="Moraes, SS, Duarte, M, 2014. Phylogeny of Neotropical Castniidae (Lepidoptera: Cossoidea: Castniidae): testing the hypothesis of the mimics as a monophyletic group and implications for the arrangement of the genera. Zoological Journal of the Linnean Society 170: 362 - 399, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1111/zoj.12102" title="Phylogeny of Neotropical Castniidae (Lepidoptera: Cossoidea: Castniidae): testing the hypothesis of the mimics as a monophyletic group and implications for the arrangement of the genera." url="https://doi.org/10.1111/zoj.12102" volume="170" year="2014">Moraes and Duarte (2014)</bibRefCitation>
synonymized the genus 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Castniidae" genus="Hista" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Hista" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">Hista</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Oiticica, 1955 with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hubner" authorityYear="1823" class="Insecta" family="Castniidae" genus="Synpalamides" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Synpalamides" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">Synpalamides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<normalizedToken originalValue="Hübner">Huebner</normalizedToken>
, [1823], an arrangement that we follow for now. This species is almost exclusively found in south-southeast Brazil, where it is usually on the wing from December to February in areas of Atlantic Forest (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.2421.1.1" author="Moraes, SS" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" pagination="1 - 27" refId="B29" refString="Moraes, SS, Duarte, M, Gonzalez, JM, 2010. Revision of Hista Oiticica (Lepidoptera: Castniidae) and discussion of the validity of its subspecies. Zootaxa 2421: 1 - 27, DOI: https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.2421.1.1" title="Revision of Hista Oiticica (Lepidoptera: Castniidae) and discussion of the validity of its subspecies." url="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.2421.1.1" volume="2421" year="2010">Moraes et al. 2010</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Penco, FC" journalOrPublisher="Edicion del autor, Moron" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" refId="B32" refString="Penco, FC, 2011. Lepidoptera Argentina. Catalogo Ilustrado y Comentado de las Mariposas de Argentina. Parte I: Castniidae. Edicion del autor, Moron" title="Lepidoptera Argentina. Catalogo Ilustrado y Comentado de las Mariposas de Argentina. Parte I: Castniidae." year="2011">Penco 2011</bibRefCitation>
). Very little is known about its biology, but its larvae are known to feed on 
<taxonomicName class="Monocotyledoneae" family="Bromeliaceae" genus="Tillandsia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Tillandsia aeronthos" order="Bromeliales" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="aeronthos">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">Tillandsia aeronthos</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Loisel.) L.B. Sm. (
<taxonomicName class="Monocotyledoneae" family="Bromeliaceae" genus="Tillandsia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Bromeliales" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="family">Bromeliaceae</taxonomicName>
) (
<bibRefCitation author="Enslen, C" journalOrPublisher="Revista do Centro de Cultura Scientifica" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" pagination="39 - 41" refId="B12" refString="Enslen, C, 1920. A biologia das Castniidae: garbei e boisduvalii (beskei). Revista do Centro de Cultura Scientifica 3: 39 - 41" title="A biologia das Castniidae: garbei e boisduvalii (beskei)." volume="3" year="1920">Enslen 1920</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Biezanko, CM" journalOrPublisher="Escola de Agronomia &quot; Eliseu Maciel &quot; (B)" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" pagination="1 - 12" refId="B4" refString="Biezanko, CM, 1961. Castniidae, Zygaenidae, Dalceridae, Eucleidae, Megalopygidae, Cossidae et Hepialidae da Zona Missioneira do Rio Grande do Sul. Arquivos de Entomologia. Escola de Agronomia &quot;Eliseu Maciel&quot; (B) 14: 1 - 12" title="Castniidae, Zygaenidae, Dalceridae, Eucleidae, Megalopygidae, Cossidae et Hepialidae da Zona Missioneira do Rio Grande do Sul. Arquivos de Entomologia." volume="14" year="1961">Biezanko 1961</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
